title: For Sale/Trade:  1942 Winchester mod. 12 16ga.
postcontent: Winchester mod. 12 16ga. 28'' full choke barrel made in 1942. Not very many of these guns were produced in 42 in any gauge due to the shift in military manufacturing for the war effort. It being a 16ga. makes it even more rare. This shotgun is in excellent (98%) condition. One small shallow dent in the stock wrist on the left side at the reciever. No rust, no blueing wear, no scratches or gouges in the wood, excellent bore, serious collector piece. Over the past 30 yrs. I have owned quiet a few of these guns in 16 ga. and examined dozens of them. None of them have even came close to being in as good a shape as this one because most all of them were used hard and put up wet. Again, this gun is a serious collector peice.

Yugoslavian PAP M59/66: Added 22 mm grenade launcher which appears visually like a flash suppressor or muzzle brake on the end of the barrel. Front sight has a fold-up "ladder" for use in grenade sighting (main sights on the A1 version have flip up phosphorus or tritium night sights). When the grenade sight is raised, the gas system is automatically blocked and the action must be manually cycledrifle grenades must be fired with blank cartridges for safety, and this feature helps ensure that a live round is not loaded from the magazine. The gas system is not automatically unblocked when the sight is folded, however, and must be manually opened to again allow semi-automatic operation.[5] Barrel was not chrome-lined before about 1970. Both the grenade launcher and grenade sight are NATO spec. Stock is typically made from beech wood. Many of the ones imported into the US were actually used in military action and as such many were in less than pristine shape or had unmatching serial numbered parts. Some have stocks that were dinged, scratched or even intentionally carved or notched by the soldiers issued the rifles, often with a variation of the Serbian coat of arms. There is some collector interest in rifles with carved or marked stocks.  I will even throw in the leaper scope that came with it, nothing fancy, just a scope!!!
